<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-389-976  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 389 976.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  June 27 1989 v3 n25 p55(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Access National Weather Service forecasts. (database )</TITLE><AUTHOR>Waring, Becky.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Metacomet Software Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Accu-Weather Forecaster (Computer program) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     United States. National Weather ServiceData BasesForecastingSoftware PackagesEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Access National Weather Service forecastsandM;The same service that provides data to many newspapers and TV stations fortheir weather forecasts also can be accessed from your Mac with Accu-WeatherForecaster.andP;  Accu-Weather is a private database that takes information andforecasts from the Nat-ional Weather Service (NWS) and redistributes them forcommercial and private use.andM;NWS computer data is cryptic and complicated to retrieve.andP;  The Forecasterprogram automates the process of dialing up, receiving and interpreting thatdata, so you only have to choose what forecasts you want and how to viewthem.andP;  The catch is that connect time is expensive; a typical request forlocal and national data costs about $2.andP;  Rates are cheaper for nighttime andpersonal use, but they still preclude using the service just for fun.andP;  Thereis also a startup fee of $39.95 to $89.95.andM;On the other hand, those who need specialized or up-to-the-minute weatherinformation will find the program useful.andP;  Temperature, barometric pressure,precipitation, wind speed and direction, dewpoint and visibility data are allavailable for any combination of local or national sites you select.andP;  You cangraph these variables over time or view them in map format.andP;  Local andnational forecasts made by NWS can also be downloaded, but you can make yourown with the program's forecasting primer.andM;Accu-Weather is easy to use and comes with an excellent manual.andO;Municipalities, educators, commodities traders, farmers, pilots and otherswill find it a handy tool.andP;  Forecaster costs $89.95 and is available fromMetacomet Software, P.O.andP;  Box 31337, Hartford, Conn.andP;  06103; (800) 782-5661.andO;</TEXT></DOC>